  <h lang="en">derived common nouns</h>
  <h lang="gd">ainmearan gnàthach bunaichte</h>
  <p>Derived common nouns are <a href="?xx=nouns/common_nouns">common nouns</a> which have been
    derived from other nouns, adjectives or verbs, typically by addition of a suffix eg. <ul>
      <li><m>ceart</m> adj. <en>correct</en> ⇒ <m>ceartas</m> masc. <en>justice</en></li>
      <li><m>seall</m> vb. <en>look</en> ⇒ <m>sealladh</m> masc. <en>view</en></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>An important subclass of derived common nouns are the <a href="?xx=nouns/verbal_nouns">verbal
      nouns</a>.</p>
  <p>Noun-deriving suffixes – <ul>
      <li><a href="?gd=_ach">-(e)ach</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_achd">-(e)achd</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_ag">-(e)ag</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_aire">-aire</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_an">-(e)an</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_as">-(e)as</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_e">-e</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_ead">-ead</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_iche">-(a)iche</a></li>
      <li><a href="?gd=_inn">-(a)inn</a></li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <p>cf. <a href="?gd=tionail">tionail</a>
    <vb/>
    <en>come/bring together, gather</en> ⇒ <a href="?gd=tional">tional</a>
    <masc/>
    <en>collection, assembly</en>, <a href="?gd=aba">aba</a>
    <masc/>
    <en>abbot</en> ⇒ <a href="?gd=abaid">abaid</a>
    <fem/>
    <en>abbey</en>.</p>
